                  </rs>.</p>
               <p>Mr. BOLLAND conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-307-person1650">
                  JOHN 
                  LINES
               <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1650" type="surname" value="LINES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1650" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1650" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of the East India Company. I was employed to watch at their warehouse in <placeName id="t18260406-307-crimeloc1651">Crutched-friars</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-307-crimeloc1651" type="placeName" value="Crutched-friars"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260406-307-crimeloc1651" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-307-off1648 t18260406-307-crimeloc1651"></join>, where some men were mending chests - they went to breakfast at ten o'clock, and soon after the prisoner came into the cellar and went to a chest - I heard his hand go into the chest three distinct times; I then went for Mr. Frazer, the elder, and said I must search the prisoner; he said he had not got any thing - but after I took him down to the counting-house he offered me a sovereign to let go his hand; I found this tea in his breeches pocket - the chest had been plundered before - he had no business in the cellar.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-307-person1651">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  FRAZER
               <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1651" type="surname" value="FRAZER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1651" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-307-person1651" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an elder. I saw the prisoner - Lines searched him in my presence, and about six ounces of black tea was taken from his left-hand breeches pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took a book from George Williams - I went to tell him he had brought a wrong number, and I asked him to change it. <rs id="t18260406-307-verdict1652" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18260406-307-verdict1652" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
